    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is achieved through clear section headers, consistent use of typography (via text styles), and strategic use of spacing and dividers. The most important settings (like personal information) are placed towards the top.  Color is used consistently, adhering to the design system's color palettes, ensuring visual harmony and clear distinction between elements."
